criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          1. patients having had generalize CP which were agreed upon by consensus at the World
             Workshop in Periodontics in 1999 [24];

          2. three or more teeth having at least two quadrants with probing depth between 4 and 6
             mm and radiographic signs of bone loss;

          3. aged 30 years and above;

          4. a minimum of 20 teeth.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          1. received periodontal therapy within the last 12 months;

          2. systemic diseases which could affect periodontal treatment outcomes;

          3. having taken systemic antibiotics within the last 6 months;

          4. pregnancy or breast-feeding for female patients.
